In this homelab, I set up and configured File Services in a Windows Server environment joined to my NK.local Active Directory domain.

The purpose of this project was to understand how file sharing works in a domain environment, how permissions are controlled, and how storage can be managed using File Server Resource Manager (FSRM).

This lab simulates a real-world company file server setup.

Lab Environment

Domain: NK.local 

Server: Windows Server (File Server role installed)

Client: Windows 10 (domain joined)

Tools Used:

File and Storage Services

Group Policy

File Server Resource Manager (FSRM)

What I Configured
1. Created a Shared Folder

I created a folder:

C:\SHARED


Then I enabled sharing and configured:

Share permission: Everyone â€“ Read

NTFS permissions:

CREATOR OWNER

SYSTEM

Administrators

Domain Users

This allowed controlled access while maintaining security.

