5. Created a File Screen

To prevent misuse of storage, I created a file screen to block:

Audio and Video files


This prevents users from storing large media files on the company file share.

ðŸ“· Screenshot:
screenshots/07-create-file-screen.png

What I Learned

Through this project, I learned:

The difference between Share permissions and NTFS permissions

How Group Policy can automate drive mapping

How quotas protect server storage

How file screening prevents unwanted file types

How enterprise file servers are structured

Project Outcome

After completing this lab:

Users can access the shared folder securely

The network drive maps automatically

Storage is limited to 10 GB

Media files are blocked

Everything is managed centrally through the domain

This project helped me better understand real-world Windows Server file management and Active Directory integration.
